<h3 style="margin-top: 35px;">privacy policy</h3>
<p class="padtop">Last Modified: May 4, 2010</p>

<p class="padtop">
PAGEONETWENTYSIX ("PAGE126", "PAGEONETWENTYSIX.COM", "PageOneTwentySix", "pageonetwentysix", who, we, or us) recognizes the importance of privacy and the sensitivity of personal information. This privacy policy outlines how we handle your personal information submitted to us and how we <a href="?func=privacy">safeguard your privacy</a>.
</p>

<ul class="encrypt_process">

	<li> COLLECTION OF PERSONAL INFORMATION<br />
	(1) When you create an account at pageonetwentysix.com ("PAGE126") you will provide PAGE126 with certain personal information including your first name, last name, and e-mail address. Additionally, you may provide PAGE126 with such information as your time zone, age, etc., (hereafter referred to as "Personal Information"). (2) When you contact PAGE126 through email or other communications, we reserve the right to store those communications in order to improve our service as well as respond to your inquiry. (4) PAGE126 will only ask for Personal Information when it is required and explain to you why it is required and how we will be using it.</li>

	<li> COLLECTION OF SITE INFORMATION<br />
	(1) When you log in to PAGE126, we collect information such as, but not limited to, your browser type, IP address, login and email. Additionally, PAGE126 also stores information from your browser using cookies (hereafter referred to as "Site Information"). (2) Cookies are pieces of data stored on the User's computer and contain information about that User's session experience. Most browsers are set up to accept cookies automatically. You can modify this setting in your browser's preferences or security options. Please read your browser's help guide for information on how to do this. However, if you do not enable cookies or javascript, you may not be able to use some of the features available on PAGE126.
	</li>

	<li> USE OF PERSONAL AND SITE INFORMATION<br />
	(1) PAGE126 collects and uses your Personal Information to communicate with you about your account. At anytime members can unsubscribe from any email communications from PAGE126 by unchecking the preference box in their settings, or by permanently deleting their account, which can be done from the settings page. (2) We do not sell, rent, exchange or share any Personal Information to third parties without your explicit consent. (3) If we wish to use your Personal Information outside of what is described in this Privacy Policy, we will request your permission and offer you the option of opting out. (4) Site Information is collected for analytical and statistical purposes only so that we can better serve our users. Cookies are used to store session data and to help with the usability of our Site. We also analyze traffic patterns and site statistics to help us decide features and provide you with a better experience. We do not collect or associate an IP addresses to Personal Information nor do we distribute or share IP information with any third party. (5) Non Personal Information may  be used to display customized content and targeted advertising. Rather, we will use Site Information and/or keywords in user content. Any information that is used to generate targeted advertising is in not disclosed to third parties nor personally identifiable.(6) PAGE126 permits third party advertisers to set and access their cookies on your computer. How these parties use their cookies is governed by their own privacy policies.
	</li>

	<li> DISCLOSURE OF PERSONAL INFORMATION<br />
	(1) PAGE126 shall disclose Personal Information under the following circumstances: (a) satisfy any applicable law, regulation, legal process or enforceable governmental request, (b) enforce the PAGE126 Terms of Use, including investigation of potential violations, such as copyright infringement, (c) address or prevent fraud, or (d) protect against harm to PAGE126, its users or the public as required or permitted by law. If any of these circumstances are discovered, PAGE126 will do our best to resolve it. (2) Any content that you make available to other users by granting access to other users to all or part of your online notebook is done so at your own risk. Any Personal Information that is posted or sent by any user is the sole responsibility of such user and PAGE126 shall not be held responsible for that, or other Personal Information that you make public.</li>

	<li> ACCURACY<br />
	(1) PAGE126 will try to ensure that Personal Information about you is accurate, complete and up-to-date. In the event that you have questions about the accuracy of your Personal Informtion we have collected about you, you verify and update it through your user settings at any time.</li>

	<li>ACCESS TO INFORMATION<br />
	Should you no longer desire to be a member of PAGE126, you may deactivate your account at any time by visiting your setting page. When deactivating your account, all content and/or Personal Information will be permently deleted by PAGE126. (2) Although, data backups performed by the PAGE126 hosting provider, phpwebhosting.com, may remain archived according to their policies. The information archived by phpwebhosting.com is not accessible by PAGE126 and therefore your content and Personal Information will remain irretrievable. (3) Users may also emailPAGE126 at support@pageonetwentysix.com and request that their account be deleted. In its sole discretion, PAGE126, reserves the right and without any notice, for any reasonto delete any account. In the event of a termination or deletion of your account, all content and Personal Information will be lost.

	<li> PRIVACY AND SECURITY OF USER CONTENT<br />
	(1) PAGE126 is committed to protecting your privacy and content. All account users have a unique account password which is stored as a one-way encrypted password in our database. <!-- In addition, each account user all has a secret key that is used to encrypt/decrypt content using 256-bit AES encryption algorithms. PAGE126 does not have access to this secret key and if it lost the encrypted content will not be able to be retrieved and PAGE126 will not be able recover your content. (2) You assume all responsibility for the maintenance and recollection of your secret key and account password. PAGE126 disclaims all responsibility and liability and any loss of data resulting from the loss of any encryption password. (3) --> Although we take measures to ensure the privacy and security of your user content, we cannot guarantee its privacy or its security, because no privacy or security measures are perfect or impenetrable. Additionally, we cannot control other users whom you have shared Personal Information or account information with, and therefore we do not guarantee that unauthorized individuals will not obtain access to your account, content or Personal Information. We are also not responsible for any circumvention of our privacy or security systems.</li>

	<li> NO CHILDREN UNDER AGE 13<br />
	(1) PAGE126 does not knowingly collect Personal Information from anyone under the age of 13 or knowingly allow such persons under the age of 13 to sign-up. If you are under 13, please do not sign-up for an account. If we discover any users under the age of 13 we will delete all Personal Information and delete their Account from the Site. If you believe that we may have any information from or about a child under 13, please <a href="?func=contact">contact us</a> at info@pageonetwentysix.com.</li>

	<li> MINORS BETWEEN THE AGES OF 13 AND 18 YEARS<br />
	(1) We require that minors over the age of 13 obtain their parents or legal guardians permission before submitting any Personal Information about themselves to not only PAGE126, but anyone over the Internet. The parents or legal guardians of the minor must agree to the PAGE126 Terms of Use on behalf of the minors.</li>

	<li> EXTERNAL WEBSITES<br />
	(1) The PAGE126 website may contain links to other external websites, including those of advertisers on the site. PAGE126 is not responsible for the privacy practices of third party websites. This Privacy Policy applies only to the information collected by PAGE126.</li>

	<li>CHANGE OF OWNERSHIP<br />
	(1) If the ownership of PAGE126 changes, in whole or part, your Personal Information and Site Information will be transferred to the new owner(s).</li>

	<li> NOTICE<br />
	(1) PAGE126 may amend this Privacy Policy at any time. New terms become effective immediately and we are not required to notify you of the changes. Your continued use of the PAGE126 after any such amendments constitutes your acceptance of the revised Privacy Policy. If you do not agree with a revised Privacy Policy immediately delete your account. It is your responsibility to regularly check this Privacy Policy. If you have any questions about PAGE126, this Privacy Policy, or the practices followed by PAGE126, please <a href="?func=contact">contact us</a> with your concerns at info@pageonetwentysix.com.</li>
	</ul>

